natural problem: What is the domain of $y=\dfrac{x^3-27}{x+27}$?  (Express your answer using interval notation.)
natural solution: The only values of $x$ that would make this fraction undefined are values that makes the denominator $0$.
Therefore, the fraction is undefined when $x+27=0$, or when $x=-27$.
